Basic idea is as follows:

Run JULES for irrigated and non-irrigated scenarios.

For the irrigated scenario we're not concerned with the source - we just need to know the maximum area that is equipped for irrigation.

Then we construct two scenarios:

(i)  Irrigation source comes from groundwater + area currently irrigated with canals
(ii) Irrigation source comes from groundwater + the maximum possible canal area
